messageBody:
Hello Fred,

I'm the one who created the dictionary that is now out
on the group's web site. If I get a chance, I will
take a look at the links below and try to build a
English version. Another thought my be to consolidate
then into on document.

If anyone has thoughts on how we could provide
notation to show U.S English and British English,
please send them along.

Chuck

--- Fred Tarbox <rtarbox@...> wrote:
> --- In Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com, "Fred Tarbox"
> <rtarbox@d...>
> wrote:
> > I think I may pay the �16.95 for Cambridge's
> Pronouncing Dictionary.
>
> Always, always, always when I make a post like this,
> something better
> comes along five minutes later. CMU comes through
> again:
>
>
http://www.speech.cs.cmu.edu/comp.speech/Section1/Lexical/beep.html
